# Credentials / secrets (defensive — none of these belong in the repo).
# pdtui keeps its live session in the OS keyring; configure-session.sh writes
# session.json under $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/pdtui and probes write to $TMPDIR, all
# outside the tree. These patterns guard against an accidental repo-local copy.
.env
.env.*
session.json
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.jks
*.keystore
id_rsa
id_rsa.pub
